# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PAI — environment variables (example)
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# Only EXPO_PUBLIC_* vars are bundled into the app at build time.
# Do NOT put server secrets (like OPENAI_API_KEY) in this app .env.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Supabase (client) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Required at startup. The app creates its single Supabase client from these
# (see template/core/client.ts). Both are public/anon-safe and shipped in the
# client bundle.
#
# Find them in: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
#   • Project URL  → EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
#   • anon public  → EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# Keep these pointed at the CURRENT (OnSpace) backend until pre-cutover
# verification is complete. The cutover is the single step of swapping these
# two values to your new Supabase project.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ── OPENAI_API_KEY — ai-quote edge function ONLY ─────────────
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is NOT an app variable. It is read server-side by the Supabase Edge
# Function `supabase/functions/ai-quote/index.ts` via Deno.env.get('OPENAI_API_KEY').
#
# • Do NOT add it to the app's .env and do NOT prefix it with EXPO_PUBLIC_.
#   Anything EXPO_PUBLIC_* is embedded in the client bundle and would leak the key.
# • Set it as a Supabase function secret instead:
#       supabase secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
#   (or via Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets)
#
# It is listed here only for documentation/discoverability.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...        # set via `supabase secrets set`, not in this file
